    en: "Missing a court date in New York usually leads to a bench warrant for arrest under Criminal Procedure Law 530.70. The good news: a warrant can often be cleared by going back to court voluntarily, sometimes with a lawyer appearing first to line things up. The sooner the warrant is addressed, the better the outcome. Ignoring it makes everything worse — a warrant does not expire, can surface at any traffic stop or background check, and can add new charges like Bail Jumping under Penal Law 215.55 through 215.57."
